<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="105">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="105">Large in size (&gt; 4 mm); mentum bearing paired foveae; pronotum quadrate, with square to acute hind angles; base of elytra wider than pronotum; elytra round, convex, with width across elytra conspicuously greatest at midpoint; ARG elongate, straight, very close to and subparallel with lateral margin of elytron.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
